  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
    <h1>About SmartPetGuide</h1>

    <p>SmartPetGuide was founded in 2026 by pet owners frustrated with fake reviews and AI-generated fluff. We research every product thoroughly — analyzing thousands of verified Amazon reviews, cross-referencing owner experiences, and comparing specs side-by-side — to give you clear, honest recommendations.</p>

    <h2>Our Story</h2>
    <p>Like most pet owners, we started as overwhelmed shoppers. Which $600 litter box is actually worth it? Does an $89 automatic feeder work as well as a $139 one? The internet was full of contradictory advice, sponsored posts disguised as reviews, and "best of" lists written by people who clearly never owned a pet.</p>
    <p>So we decided to fix that. SmartPetGuide is the site we wish existed when we were shopping — honest comparisons, thorough research, and clear recommendations based on evidence, not affiliate commissions.</p>

    <h2>How We Review</h2>
    <p>Every product we cover goes through a structured research process:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Verified review analysis:</strong> We aggregate and analyze thousands of verified-purchase reviews across Amazon and other retailers. When hundreds of owners report the same motor failure or the same praise for quiet operation, we flag it prominently.</li>
      <li><strong>Owner experience synthesis:</strong> We cross-reference owner feedback from Reddit, forums, YouTube reviews, and social media to identify real-world patterns that spec sheets don't capture — like "cat refused to use it after week 2" or "app disconnects every update."</li>
      <li><strong>Specification & feature comparison:</strong> We compare product specs, features, and design decisions across competing models to help you understand what you're actually paying for at each price point.</li>
      <li><strong>Cost-of-ownership analysis:</strong> Upfront price is only part of the story. We calculate 3-year total costs including replacement filters, disposable trays, subscription fees, and typical lifespan based on owner-reported replacement rates.</li>
      <li><strong>Amazon data verification:</strong> Every product we recommend is validated against real-time Amazon data — Best Sellers Rank, rating trends, review volume, and price history — to ensure our picks reflect what actually sells and what owners actually rate highly.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Why Trust Us?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Independent:</strong> We are not owned by any pet brand, retailer, or manufacturer. Our recommendations are based on research, not partnerships.</li>
      <li><strong>Transparent:</strong> Every article clearly discloses our affiliate relationships. We earn commissions from qualifying Amazon purchases — at zero cost to you.</li>
      <li><strong>Evidence-based:</strong> We cite real Amazon review counts, Best Sellers Ranks, and verified purchase data. No vague "we loved it" statements without specifics.</li>
      <li><strong>Updated:</strong> All articles carry a 2026 date stamp and are regularly updated when new models launch or prices change.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our Research Team</h2>
    <p>Our reviews are researched and written by long-time pet owners who have collectively analyzed 50+ smart pet devices. Our team includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A multi-cat household owner tracking litter box performance data across multiple models and brands</li>
      <li>A Golden Retriever owner comparing GPS tracker accuracy on daily off-leash hikes</li>
      <li>A tech-focused cat owner evaluating app-controlled fountains and health-monitoring litter boxes</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Make Money</h2>
    <p>SmartPetGuide participates in the Amazon Associates program. When you click our links and buy a product, we earn a small commission — typically 3-5% of the purchase price. This costs you nothing extra and directly funds our research. We also plan to join additional affiliate networks (ShareASale, Impact) to diversify our revenue.</p>
    <p><strong>Our editorial integrity promise:</strong> We never accept payment for reviews, sponsored placements, or "paid to promote" deals. Products are researched independently. Our rankings are based on evidence, not commission rates.</p>

